	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thye problem with augmentation of death is mana cost and Refresh on spell.&nbsp;&nbsp;the second one being the bigger concern for me most of the time.  I always seam to lose pet buff just as I start fear kiting something.  And if ytou don't have the buff loaded, eatting up a slot, your going to play hell sitting, memming, waiting for it to cycle, and cast it on your pet.  I mean I do it all the time, but it sux.  <br><br>This effect would rock if it where the lvl55 verision.  But as it is I'll really only use it when in an emergency (like in the above situation) or when chain casting pets on a raid, and maybe not even then because of the cast time.<br><br>On a side note it sure would be nice if you could buff other peoples pets.  Imaginge that only one of your 2 or three necro's had to have Augmentation of death loaded.  Or only one mage needed his best burn out loaded...<br><br>Oh well, what do I know really anyway?<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Mar  8 16:56:22 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Phelon Lvl 56 Necro of www.TriuneGuild.com<br>Mathazar Lvl 34 Monk<br>Morell Thule</td></tr>
